{"id":77,"parent_id":74,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":77,"title":"John 3: \"Ye Must Be Born Again\"","subtitle":"","short_title":"John 3: \"Ye Must Be Born Again\"","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again"},[".heading",{"id":"head4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.head4"},["h1","John 3"],[".subtitle","“Ye Must Be Born Again”"],[".intro","Some of the most basic questions in religion are: Is there a God? Does He know or care about me? What would He have me do? Is there a heaven? If so, how do I qualify to go there? A Pharisee named Nicodemus had some of those same questions. He went to Jesus by night, we presume, so that other Pharisees would not see him. As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3"},"John 3"],", look for what Jesus taught him."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f12"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3"},"John 3"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Listeth"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Wants, chooses"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Master"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Teacher"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Lest"],"(v. 20)"],["td","For fear that, because they are afraid that"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Reproved"],"(v. 20)"],["td","Punished, be told they are wrong"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Tarried"],"(v. 22)"],["td","Stayed"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Purifying"],"(v. 25)"],["td","Baptism and other ceremonial cleansings"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","By measure"],"(v. 34)"],["td","In smaller amounts"],["td"]]]]],[".",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-077-2.gif"}],[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","Qumran purification font."]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.8"},"John 3:8"],"—“The Wind Bloweth Where It Listeth”"],["p.para",{"id":"p81","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.p81"},"It is difficult to explain how it feels to feel the Spirit. Jesus compared it to trying to tell someone about the wind, as the accompanying illustration shows."]]],[".figure",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f14"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["th",{"colspan":"2"},["p.para",["b","It is not seen by the eye, yet we perceive its operation. We feel it; we sense it. We know it exists by the effects it produces. It can be gentle or very powerful."]]]],["tr",["td",["p.para",["b","The Holy Ghost"]]],["td",["p.para"],[".",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-077-3.gif"}],["p.para",{"id":"p85","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.p85"},["b","The Wind"]]],["p"]]]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f16"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["p.para"],[".",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-078-1.gif"}]],["p"]],["td",["p.para"],[".",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-078-2.gif"}]],["p"]]]]]],["p.para",{"id":"p88","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.p88"},["span.emphasis","The serpent Moses put on a pole was a symbol for the Savior. Just as looking upon the serpent saved the Israelites from physical death, looking to Christ can save us from physical and spiritual death."]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p89","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.p89"},"Do activity A and one other activity (B–D) as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3"},"John 3"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a-mastery.gif"}],"Scripture Mastery—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.5"},"John 3:5"]],[".figure",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f19"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.2"},"John 3:2"],", how did Nicodemus know that Jesus was “from God”?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What did Jesus say was a more sure way of “seeing”? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.3"},"v. 3"],")."]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","What did Nicodemus say that indicates he was not thinking spiritually when he began speaking with Jesus?"]],["li",["span.label","4."],["p.para","Find at least two scriptures that explain the two kinds of baptism Jesus said we must receive (use the helps available in the LDS editions of the scriptures to find them)."]],["li",["span.label","5."],["p.para","Why do you think Nicodemus went to Jesus “by night” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.2"},"v. 2"],")?"]],["li",["span.label","6."],["p.para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/19.38-40"},"John 19:38–40"],". Do you think Nicodemus believed what Jesus taught him? Explain your answer."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"For God So Loved the World"],[".figure",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f20"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.16-17"},"John 3:16–17"],", what is one way we know how much God loves us?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What do those verses teach us about what Heavenly Father and Jesus want to do for all people?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","Explain how you think people would perish if Jesus had not come into the world."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-c.gif"}],"Light versus Dark"],[".figure",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f21"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","In your own words, write at least two statements of truth that explain principles Jesus taught in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.19-21"},"John 3:19–21"],"."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Give an example from your life, or from things you have seen, of how each of the statements are true. (You do not have to use people’s names in your examples.)"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-d.gif"}],"Lessons from a Great Prophet"],["p.para",{"id":"p101","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.p101"},"From",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/3.25-33"},"John 3:25–33"],", list the lessons you think leaders, teachers, and missionaries could learn from what John the Baptist said and did. Include the verses where you found each idea."]]]],[".resources",[".",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-3-ye-must-be-born-again.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-078-3.gif"}]]]]]],"refs":null}
